# eid0l0n — example environment file
#
# As of 0.8.0, eid0l0n does NOT read any image-API keys. The host agent
# uses its own image-gen tool (MCP / curl / local ComfyUI / etc.) on the
# instructions JSON emitted by generate.py — credentials live wherever
# that tool keeps them. The built-in Codex backend reads ~/.codex/auth.json
# (managed by `codex login`), not env.
#
# Only a handful of EIDOLON_* knobs survive, all path/quality overrides.
# Copy to <workspace>/eidolon/env (mode 600) or to a .env in your shell.
# An `env` file in the workspace is auto-loaded by setup.py / generate.py.

# ─── Path overrides (rarely needed) ──────────────────────────────────────────

# Full state-dir override (dev/test escape hatch). Default: <cwd>/eidolon/.
# EIDOLON_HOME=/some/path/eidolon

# Override the saved visual_anchor.md path. Default: <state-dir>/visual_anchor.md.
# EIDOLON_VISUAL_ANCHOR=/path/to/visual_anchor.md

# Override the saved reference image path. Default: from anchor's `reference:` header.
# EIDOLON_REFERENCE=/path/to/reference.jpg

# Output-dir override (point PNGs at a separate disk while state stays in workspace).
# Default: same as state dir.
# EIDOLON_OUTPUT_DIR=~/Pictures/eidolon
